loudspeaker /ˌlaʊdˈspiːkə/

CET6+ TEM4 (loudspeakers) 

1. N-COUNT A loudspeaker is a piece of electronic equipment that forms part of a public address system and transmits sound. 扬声器 

例： The loudspeaker announced the arrival of the train. 广播说火车进站了。 

2. N-COUNT A loudspeaker is a piece of equipment, for example, part of a radio or hi-fi system, through which sound comes out. 喇叭 [英国英语]

